sl:listdef.name: ATU
sl:listdef.sl:lit: Adam Falkenstein, "Archaische Texte aus Uruk" (ATU 1), Berlin 1936.
sl:listdef.sl:note: Signs in ATU 1 are referred to as, e.g., ATU001; texts in ATU are referred to as, e.g., ATU 1, 1.

sl:listdef.name: BAU
sl:listdef.sl:lit: E. Burrows, Archaic Texts (Ur Excavations Texts 2), London 1935.
sl:listdef.sl:note: BAU is aligned to AP designations; CDLI UET 2 transliterations do not always match these. For example, BAU104=I≈†~b1, BAU105=I≈†~b2 but UET 2 transliterations generally use I≈†~a for both forms. Alignments with CDLI-tc are sometimes approximate, e.g., BAU278=SILA‚ÇÑ~b; BAU311=AD~a.

sl:listdef.name: U+
sl:listdef.sl:lit: Unofficial unicode codepoints used in AP23.

sl:listdef.name: ZATU
sl:listdef.sl:lit: M. W. Green und Hans J. Nissen, unter Mitarbeit von Peter Damerow und Robert K. Englund, "Zeichenliste der Archaischen Texte aus Uruk" (ATU 2), Berlin 1987.

sl:sysdef.name: AP23
sl:sysdef.sl:info: Anshuman Pandey's CDLI-NAME field as used in the proposal L2/23-190

sl:sysdef.name: ATFU-S
sl:sysdef.sl:info: ATFU sign name for PCSL sign
sl:sysdef.sl:lit: C. Lecompte and L. Verderame (ed.) Archaic Tablets and Fragments from Ur. (Nisaba 25). Messina, 2013.
sl:sysdef.sl:note: Because the ATFU sign list is unnumbered we use @sys ATFU-S entries to catalogue ATFU 113-126, Section VII, ‚ÄúIndex of Signs‚Äù, which lists the signs occurring in the tablets published in Nisaba 25. The signs are not numbered and are referenced by name.

sl:sysdef.name: CDLI-tc
sl:sysdef.sl:info: CDLI text corpus--the CDLI transliterations of Uruk IV and Uruk III texts
sl:sysdef.sl:note: This corpus is available at https://cdli.mpiwg-berlin.mpg.de/ or at http://oracc.org/pcsl. Transliteration conventions do not always match CDLI-gh.

sl:sysdef.name: CUSAS01
sl:sysdef.sl:info: S.F. Monaco, The Cornell University Archaic Tablets (CUSAS 1), Bethesda, MD, 2007.
sl:sysdef.sl:note: Additional signs on pages 15, ‚ÄúNew Signs and Sign Variants‚Äù and 281, ‚ÄúNew Signs and Variants‚Äù.

sl:sysdef.name: CUSAS21
sl:sysdef.sl:info: S.F. Monaco, Archaic Bullae and Tablets in the Cornell University Collections (CUSAS 21), Bethesda, MD, 2014.
sl:sysdef.sl:note: Additional signs on page 166, ‚ÄúNew Signs and Variants‚Äù.

sl:sysdef.name: CUSAS31
sl:sysdef.sl:info: S.F. Monaco, Archaic Cuneiform Tablets from Private Collections (CUSAS 31), Bethesda, MD, 2016.
sl:sysdef.sl:note: Additional signs on page 203, ‚ÄúNew Signs and Variants‚Äù.

sl:sysdef.name: LLATU
sl:sysdef.sl:info: Lexicalischen Listen der Archaischen Texte aus Uruk
sl:sysdef.sl:lit: Pp.177-327 in Robert K. Englund und Hans J. Nissen unter Mitarbeit von Peter Damerow, "Die Lexikalischen Listen der Archaischen Texte aus Uruk" (ATU 3), Berlin 1993.
sl:sysdef.sl:note: The definitive edition of lexical texts from Uruk has its own sign index in which signs are often further differentiated compared to ZATU by adding lowercase letters. The signs are not numbered as a signlist but are listed alphabetically with references.
